---
description: Check for existing files before creating. Be conservative about new files and code.
alwaysApply: true
---

Before creating any file, check if similar functionality exists. Use search/glob to find existing files. Ask if user wants to modify existing or create new.

Only create files that are explicitly requested or required by a task. Keep code in the file that uses it — don't extract into a new file unless there's a clear reuse need.

Prefer less code. Don't create abstractions or files "for future use." Look for reuse and refactoring opportunities before writing new code. When in doubt, don't create it.

Before writing new styles or components, check how similar things are already done in the codebase and follow existing patterns.

**New folders and naming:** Do not invent folder names that don't exist elsewhere in the codebase. Before creating a subfolder, check how the closest existing feature of the same type organizes the same concept and mirror it. See **`docs/folder-structure.md`** for the canonical map.
